fix: bug fixes, security hardening, leaner build

Bug fixes:
- Fixed log file never rotating between runs (setup_logger now replaces old handler)
- Fixed stale dropdown after removing account (resets to "All Accounts")
- Fixed Chrome staying running on app close (quit active driver on exit)
- Fixed remove_credential return value ignored (GUI now checks bool result)
- Fixed add_credential showing wrong error (distinguishes "exists" vs save failure)
- Fixed dead JSONDecodeError catch (replaced with ValueError)
- Fixed results label green even with errors (amber when errors > 0)

Security:
- Atomic credential file writes via tempfile + os.replace() (prevents corruption)

Code quality:
- Merged Excel double I/O into single save (formatting applied in-memory)
- Extracted _build_lock_card helper (lock screen / reset password dedup)
- Extracted _create_dialog helper (settings / help dialog dedup)
- Extracted _JS_LAST_CALENDAR constant (4 repeated JS snippets)
- Consistent f-string formatting in selenium_utils.py
- Removed redundant os.makedirs on BASE_DIR in _save_last_run

Optimisation:
- Partial PDF downloads (0-byte files) now re-downloaded instead of skipped

Build:
- Synced 6 --exclude-module flags from .spec into CI workflow (unittest, xmlrpc, pydoc, ftplib, imaplib, smtplib)
- Excluded asyncio/_asyncio (not imported by any dependency)
- Moved selenium browser cleanup (firefox/edge/ie/safari) from --exclude-module to post-build deletion (avoids import errors)
- Fixed Tcl/Tk pruning paths (_tcl_data/_tk_data, not tcl/tk — was a no-op on CI)
- Tcl/Tk pruning: msgs, tzdata, demos, stock images, opt, http packages
- CJK encoding pruning: kept 8 Western .enc files, removed 74 CJK/legacy files
- Build reduced from 16.2 MB to ~13 MB zipped (27 MB unzipped)

Version:
- Bumped APP_VER to v1.2.1
